HEADWORD: Septuagenary
<hw>Sep`tu*ag"e*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>septuagenarius</ets>, fr. <ets>septuageny</ets> seventy each; akin
to <ets>septuaginta</ets> seventy, <ets>septem</ets> seven. See
<er>Seven</er>.]</ety> <def>Consisting of seventy; also, seventy years
old.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A
septuagenarian.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

